{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Werte","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute/Values","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"maßangaben","title":"<a id=\"massangaben\" name=\"massangaben\">Maßangaben</a>","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Für Angaben von Größen und Abständen in den Attributen der Darstellungselemente kennt MathML verschiedene Maßeinheiten und Konstanten:</p>","titleAsText":"Maßangaben"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"einheiten","title":"Einheiten","isH3":true,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th>Einheit</th>\n   <th>Beschreibung</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>em</code></td>\n   <td>Einheit, die sich auf die Schriftgröße bezieht. 1 em entspricht etwa der Breite des Großbuchstabens M. Siehe auch <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/CSS/font-size\"><code>font-size</code></a>.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>ex</code></td>\n   <td>Einheit, die sich auf die Schriftgröße bezieht. 1 ex entspricht etwa der Höhe des Kleinbuchstabens x. In vielen Schriftarten gilt auch <code>1ex ≈ 0.5em</code>. Siehe auch <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/CSS/font-size\"><code>font-size</code></a>.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>px</code></td>\n   <td>Pixel (Bildschirmpunkte)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>in</code></td>\n   <td>Zoll (1 Zoll = 2,54 Zentimeter)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>cm</code></td>\n   <td>Zentimeter</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>mm</code></td>\n   <td>Millimeter</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>pt</code></td>\n   <td>Punkt (1 Punkt = 1/72 Zoll)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>pc</code></td>\n   <td>Pica (1 Pica = 12 Punkt)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>%</code></td>\n   <td>Prozent vom Standardwert.</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"konstanten","title":"Konstanten","isH3":true,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th>Konstante</th>\n   <th>Wert</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>veryverythinmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>1/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>verythinmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>2/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>thinmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>3/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>mediummathspace</code></td>\n   <td>4/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>thickmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>5/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>verythickmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>6/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>veryverythickmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>7/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th colspan=\"2\">Negative Konstante, seit Gecko 7.0 (Firefox 7.0 / Thunderbird 7.0 / SeaMonkey 2.4) (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=650530\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Bug&nbsp;650530</a>)</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>negativeveryverythinmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>-1/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>negativeverythinmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>-2/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>negativethinmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>-3/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>negativemediummathspace</code></td>\n   <td>-4/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>negativethickmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>-5/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>negativeverythickmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>-6/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>negativeveryverythickmathspace</code></td>\n   <td>-7/18<code>em</code></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Anmerkung: Namedspace gilt in MathML 3 als veraltet (siehe <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/MathML3/chapter3.html#id.3.3.4.2.1\" rel=\"external noopener\">Namedspace binding is deprecated</a>) und wird seit Gecko 15.0 nicht mehr unterstützt (Firefox 15.0 / Thunderbird 15.0 / SeaMonkey 2.12) (<a class=\"external\" href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=673759\" rel=\"external noopener\">bug 673759</a>).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"siehe_auch","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/MathML\" title=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML\">MathML</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/MathML/Element\">MathML Element-Referenz</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute\">MathML Attribut-Referenz</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"<a id=\"massangaben\" name=\"massangaben\">Maßangaben</a>","id":"maßangaben"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"siehe_auch"}],"summary":"Für Angaben von Größen und Abständen in den Attributen der Darstellungselemente kennt MathML verschiedene Maßeinheiten und Konstanten:","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"MathML Attribute Values","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Valeurs","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Values","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/mathml/attribute/values","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/mathml/attribute/values/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/MathML","title":"MathML"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute","title":"MathML Attribut-Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/MathML/Attribute/Values","title":"Werte"}],"pageTitle":"Werte - MathML | MDN","noIndexing":false}}